01:02:35,719 --> 01:02:37,391
Yes, fine. I'll get him.

746
01:02:37,599 --> 01:02:39,317
Bobby? It's your mother.

747
01:02:39,559 --> 01:02:40,833
Okay.

748
01:02:43,759 --> 01:02:45,317
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi, honey.

749
01:02:45,799 --> 01:02:48,359
- Have you missed me?
- Of course I have.

750
01:02:48,879 --> 01:02:51,393
But I'm trying not to be too sad.

751
01:02:51,799 --> 01:02:53,437
Oh, good.

752
01:02:53,639 --> 01:02:55,914
- Brush your teeth.
- I did.

753
01:02:56,119 --> 01:02:57,393
Good boy.

754
01:02:57,639 --> 01:03:01,951
I can't chat all night. There's
a cocktail party for us delegates...

755
01:03:02,159 --> 01:03:04,719
...down in the ballroom and I'm...

756
01:03:05,679 --> 01:03:06,907
Are you there?

757
01:03:07,119 --> 01:03:09,838
I dropped the phone.
I love you, Bobby!

758
01:03:10,799 --> 01:03:11,948
Don...!

759
01:03:18,399 --> 01:03:19,912
That's funny.

760
01:03:22,599 --> 01:03:24,271
Got cut off.

761
01:03:34,799 --> 01:03:36,869
That 2000... .

762
01:03:37,959 --> 01:03:41,634
- It's traveling money, isn't it?
- Yeah, it is.

763
01:03:46,039 --> 01:03:50,271
I lied to you. I didn't tell you
about the lost pet sign I saw.

764
01:03:50,479 --> 01:03:51,434
I know.

765
01:03:53,439 --> 01:03:55,350
When will you leave?

766
01:03:55,599 --> 01:03:57,954
Tomorrow, when your mother gets back.

767
01:03:58,159 --> 01:04:02,072
Collect my winnings from Len Files
at the Corner Pocket...

768
01:04:02,279 --> 01:04:03,268
...then go.

769
01:04:05,479 --> 01:04:07,595
Will I ever see you again?

770
01:04:09,039 --> 01:04:10,267
No.

771
01:04:11,759 --> 01:04:14,068
And wishing can't make it so.

772
01:04:22,279 --> 01:04:24,554
I don't want you to go.

773
01:04:29,079 --> 01:04:31,547
It's all for the best, kiddo.

774
01:04:31,759 --> 01:04:33,670
It's all for the best.

775
01:04:57,879 --> 01:05:01,838
"In yet another startling
development in Washington...

776
01:05:02,039 --> 01:05:06,715
...J. Edgar Hoover, the director of
the Federal Bureau of Investigation...

777
01:05:06,919 --> 01:05:10,958
...today issued a statement denying
the Bureau was involved...

778
01:05:11,159 --> 01:05:15,550
...in recruiting psychics
in the battle against Communism. "

779
01:05:22,399 --> 01:05:25,914
That's really what all this is about,
isn't it, Ted?

780
01:05:32,879 --> 01:05:34,597
Want a root beer?

781
01:05:35,479 --> 01:05:40,189
That's the only good thing about you
going. I can't stand that stuff.

782
01:05:40,999 --> 01:05:42,398
Yeah, I know.

783
01:05:43,719 --> 01:05:46,472
- Do you know everything?
- Nope.

784
01:05:48,479 --> 01:05:51,073
So what happens when you touch people?

785
01:05:51,639 --> 01:05:55,757
I pass on a kind of window
into other people's minds.

786
01:05:57,319 --> 01:06:00,311
Is that why they want you?
This window?

787
01:06:00,559 --> 01:06:04,677
Yeah. I know certain things,
see certain things.

788
01:06:04,879 --> 01:06:08,349
Some see it as a gift,
but to me it's always been a burden.

789
01:06:08,559 --> 01:06:10,914
What I see has a value for some.

790
01:06:11,639 --> 01:06:13,869
Maybe I escaped them this time.

791
01:06:14,079 --> 01:06:15,273
Thanks.

792
01:06:16,599 --> 01:06:17,952
Cheers.

793
01:06:18,279 --> 01:06:19,712
To good health.

794
01:06:22,279 --> 01:06:23,678
Oh, well.

795
01:06:24,359 --> 01:06:26,919
We're all just passing through, kiddo.

796
01:06:28,039 --> 01:06:30,269
Just passing through, that's all.

797
01:06:32,919 --> 01:06:35,672
Tell Carol I'd like to
say goodbye to her.

798
01:06:35,879 --> 01:06:36,914
Sure.

799
01:06:42,599 --> 01:06:44,590
- Hey, Bobby!
- Yeah?

800
01:06:46,119 --> 01:06:48,587
I think you should go find her now.

801
01:06:50,199 --> 01:06:51,427
Okay.

802
01:07:24,279 --> 01:07:26,588
- Hey, Bobby.
- Is Carol home?

803
01:07:26,799 --> 01:07:28,994
No, she went to the ravine
to read...

804
01:07:29,199 --> 01:07:30,757
...by the tree.

805
01:07:56,999 --> 01:07:59,877
You don't scare me, Bobby Garfield.

806
01:08:00,079 --> 01:08:02,274
If it isn't the Gerber Baby.

807
01:08:06,959 --> 01:08:08,358
No! Please!

808
01:08:10,599 --> 01:08:11,554
Harry?

809
01:08:27,439 --> 01:08:29,316
Carol! Carol!

810
01:08:46,839 --> 01:08:49,114
Is everything okay?

811
01:08:50,199 --> 01:08:53,236
He hit me, Bobby. He hit me hard.

812
01:08:53,439 --> 01:08:54,667
It's okay.

813
01:08:55,239 --> 01:08:57,150
- I'll go get help!
- No, please!

814
01:08:57,679 --> 01:09:00,147
Don't leave me alone.
He might come back.

815
01:09:00,359 --> 01:09:01,428
It'll be okay.

816
01:09:01,639 --> 01:09:03,038
Can you walk?

817
01:09:03,239 --> 01:09:04,149
I don't know.

818
01:09:04,359 --> 01:09:07,112
- Just try, okay?
- Maybe, I don't know.

819
01:09:10,759 --> 01:09:11,794
It'll be okay.

820
01:09:12,079 --> 01:09:14,957
It's okay.
Here, try and stand up, okay?

821
01:09:25,159 --> 01:09:28,310
You have to get on my back, okay?

822
01:09:28,559 --> 01:09:32,552
- Bobby, I can't!
- Yes, you can.

823
01:09:33,719 --> 01:09:34,708
You can.

824
01:09:34,919 --> 01:09:38,275
You have to think about
something else, okay?

825
01:09:39,919 --> 01:09:41,830
Here, get on my back.

826
01:09:42,159 --> 01:09:45,390
Remember at school how we
rode piggyback at recess?

827
01:09:45,639 --> 01:09:48,107
- Yeah.
- This is just like that, okay?

828
01:10:10,879 --> 01:10:13,916
- Bronko Nagurski.
- Nagurski.

829
01:10:21,199 --> 01:10:22,871
Ten yards...

830
01:10:23,079 --> 01:10:25,434
...seven yards...

831
01:10:30,079 --> 01:10:32,468
Nothing could stop him.

832
01:11:02,799 --> 01:11:03,834
Ted!

833
01:11:06,679 --> 01:11:07,873
Help.

834
01:11:08,199 --> 01:11:09,837
I think her arm's broken.

835
01:11:10,039 --> 01:11:12,109
Come on, Carol. It's all right.

836
01:11:25,799 --> 01:11:26,993
It's all right.

837
01:11:28,479 --> 01:11:29,958
My arm.

838
01:11:30,159 --> 01:11:32,354
Bobby, take her hand, all right?

839
01:11:34,719 --> 01:11:35,993
Oh, yes.

840
01:11:37,159 --> 01:11:40,037
One great, big boy
against one little girl.

841
01:11:40,359 --> 01:11:44,830
He's probably so afraid of you.
Thought you had the heart of a lion.

842
01:11:45,159 --> 01:11:47,115
He hurt me, Ted.

843
01:11:47,319 --> 01:11:49,674
I know. Believe me, I know.

844
01:11:50,119 --> 01:11:54,431
Now listen. I've got to look
at your shoulder. Understand?

845
01:11:54,639 --> 01:11:56,357
I don't want to hurt you.

846
01:11:57,639 --> 01:11:59,391
Oh, my.

847
01:11:59,759 --> 01:12:01,556
He broke my arm.

848
01:12:01,759 --> 01:12:04,193
No, I think it's just dislocated.

849
01:12:04,839 --> 01:12:06,591
And I think I can fix it.

850
01:12:09,079 --> 01:12:11,798
Are you a doctor, Ted?

851
01:12:11,999 --> 01:12:13,478
No, I'm not a doctor.

852
01:12:14,079 --> 01:12:16,547
But as you noted, I'm very strange.

853
01:12:16,759 --> 01:12:18,875
So who knows what I can do?

854
01:12:19,199 --> 01:12:21,429
Do you have the heart of a lion?

855
01:12:24,959 --> 01:12:27,473
Just close your eyes
and try to relax.

856
01:12:27,679 --> 01:12:30,068
Bobby, give me your belt.

857
01:12:31,519 --> 01:12:34,670
Now, Carol, do you know
what pain does?

858
01:12:34,879 --> 01:12:37,234
It rises and travels up the body.

859
01:12:38,039 --> 01:12:39,836
That's it. Thank you.

860
01:12:40,039 --> 01:12:41,631
Listen to me, Carol.

861
01:12:41,839 --> 01:12:43,716
Just listen and relax.

862
01:12:43,919 --> 01:12:46,638
I want you to bite down hard
on the belt.

863
01:12:46,839 --> 01:12:51,151
You're going to bite down
on Bobby's belt and catch the pain.

864
01:12:52,039 --> 01:12:53,677
Now relax.

865
01:12:53,879 --> 01:12:55,517
Close your eyes.

866
01:12:55,719 --> 01:12:57,198
Keep them closed.

867
01:12:57,399 --> 01:12:59,754
You're safe. Just breathe in.

868
01:13:00,399 --> 01:13:03,550
Breathe out. That's it.
There's no pain.

869
01:13:03,839 --> 01:13:06,273
Just listen to my voice.

870
01:13:07,999 --> 01:13:10,832
I can sense them
closing in on me, Bobby.

871
01:13:11,559 --> 01:13:14,710
I know. There's signs everywhere.

872
01:13:14,959 --> 01:13:16,312
Here we go.

873
01:13:16,559 --> 01:13:19,198
Bite down hard and catch... Here we go.

874
01:13:22,919 --> 01:13:24,147
All right.

875
01:13:24,639 --> 01:13:25,594
There.

876
01:13:25,799 --> 01:13:27,198
Ted?

877
01:13:27,719 --> 01:13:29,869
It doesn't hurt anymore.

878
01:13:30,719 --> 01:13:32,835
You do have the heart of a lion.

879
01:13:33,599 --> 01:13:35,271
You did well, kiddo.

880
01:13:35,519 --> 01:13:37,749
What the hell is going on in here?

881
01:13:38,639 --> 01:13:40,470
Mom, what happened to you?

882
01:13:40,679 --> 01:13:45,230
- Take your hands off that little girl!
- Mom, he didn't do anything bad!

883
01:13:45,559 --> 01:13:47,834
How dare you touch her!

884
01:13:48,039 --> 01:13:49,677
He didn't hurt her!

885
01:13:49,879 --> 01:13:52,393
I brought her so Ted could help her!

886
01:13:52,639 --> 01:13:56,268
Go to your room!
And you! You are going to jail!

887
01:13:56,519 --> 01:13:59,352
What happened to you
didn't happen to her.

888
01:14:00,159 --> 01:14:02,957
- Why's her blouse open?
- Her shoulder's hurt!

889
01:14:03,159 --> 01:14:04,877
I said, go to your room!

890
01:14:05,079 --> 01:14:07,035
What Bobby said was true!

891
01:14:09,439 --> 01:14:11,953
Let's clean you up in the bathroom.

892
01:14:12,279 --> 01:14:14,554
He carried me up the hill.

893
01:14:14,759 --> 01:14:16,954
Ted took my pain away.

894
01:14:17,159 --> 01:14:18,831
Don't you touch her!

895
01:14:20,319 --> 01:14:21,547
Go in the bathroom.

896
01:14:21,759 --> 01:14:24,796
I'm calling the police
to tell them everything.

897
01:14:25,159 --> 01:14:27,354
Tell them what happened to you.

898
01:14:28,679 --> 01:14:31,147
You weren't there. You couldn't know.

899
01:14:31,359 --> 01:14:32,792
I know.

900
01:14:32,999 --> 01:14:36,514
I know you didn't realize
the seminar would involve that.

901
01:14:36,719 --> 01:14:40,678
And I know he's growing up
while your mind is on other things.

902
01:14:44,559 --> 01:14:49,269
I'm taking that child home. And you
better not be here when I get back.

903
01:14:56,799 --> 01:14:59,677
- Be careful.
- I'll be fine, don't worry.

904
01:14:59,879 --> 01:15:02,029
Where will you go till it's dark?

905
01:15:02,239 --> 01:15:06,755
The diner near the Corner Pocket,
I guess. Pick up my winnings later.

906
01:15:07,519 --> 01:15:09,430
I want to go with you.

907
01:15:10,199 --> 01:15:12,030
Bobby, come inside, please.

908
01:15:12,719 --> 01:15:14,357
Do as she says, kiddo.

909
01:15:59,199 --> 01:16:01,235
Yes, is this...

910
01:16:01,439 --> 01:16:03,748
...Housatonic-5837?

911
01:16:05,079 --> 01:16:07,957
Yes, well, I have some information
for you...

912
01:16:08,159 --> 01:16:10,548
...about Brautigan.

913
01:16:11,079 --> 01:16:14,389
You can find him at
the Corner Pocket tonight...

914
01:16:14,639 --> 01:16:16,038
...in Bridgeport.

915
01:16:16,959 --> 01:16:19,598
Yes. Now, there's a reward...?

916
01:16:19,879 --> 01:16:20,834
Hello?

917
01:16:21,039 --> 01:16:22,074
Hello...

918
01:16:26,639 --> 01:16:28,311
Bastards.

919
01:17:00,159 --> 01:17:02,195
When your mother writes "bad"...

920
01:17:02,399 --> 01:17:05,994
...under a mental picture of someone,
she writes it in ink.

921
01:17:08,639 --> 01:17:12,154
I mean, I knew that, but
I didn't think she'd betray me.

922
01:17:17,359 --> 01:17:19,919
See, I need the money to survive...

923
01:17:20,919 --> 01:17:23,672
...and I can't go back
to the Corner Pocket.

924
01:17:24,679 --> 01:17:27,239
And I need time to think...

925
01:17:28,159 --> 01:17:29,911
...and there isn't any.

926
01:17:37,719 --> 01:17:39,277
Here's what you do.

927
01:17:40,359 --> 01:17:41,917
Write a note for me.

928
01:17:42,119 --> 01:17:43,188
A note?

929
01:17:43,959 --> 01:17:46,029
Yeah, to the Corner Pocket.

930
01:17:46,559 --> 01:17:48,390
I'll get you your money.

931
01:17:50,239 --> 01:17:53,037
I'm not sure this is a good idea.

932
01:17:53,639 --> 01:17:55,197
Ted, take my hands.

933
01:17:56,719 --> 01:18:00,997
Don't worry. I won't let
the bogeymen get you.

934
01:18:34,279 --> 01:18:35,678
Hello?

935
01:18:38,679 --> 01:18:40,431
Can I help you?

936
01:18:40,879 --> 01:18:44,667
It's about Brautigan.
He took the train. I saw him go.

937
01:18:44,879 --> 01:18:47,188
Stay out of this, kid.

938
01:18:47,399 --> 01:18:49,708
Brautigan 's our business.

939
01:18:52,519 --> 01:18:54,271
Don't hurt him.

940
01:18:56,199 --> 01:18:59,236
Please don't hurt him.

941
01:18:59,639 --> 01:19:01,550
Go home, Bobby.

942
01:20:50,639 --> 01:20:52,516
Ted, I got the money!

943
01:21:04,679 --> 01:21:06,158
Ted!

944
01:21:25,399 --> 01:21:27,674
I wouldn't have missed a minute!

945
01:21:27,919 --> 01:21:29,272
Not a single minute!

946
01:21:30,919 --> 01:21:33,194
Not for the whole world!

947
01:21:58,999 --> 01:22:01,559
Where have you been?
I've been worried!

948
01:22:01,759 --> 01:22:03,875
I'm all safe and sound.

949
01:22:04,079 --> 01:22:07,708
Do you have any idea
what you just put me through?

950
01:22:07,919 --> 01:22:11,355
You only think about yourself!

951
01:22:12,439 --> 01:22:13,997
- Bobby...
- Ted's gone.

952
01:22:14,199 --> 01:22:16,315
I'll never see him again.

953
01:22:17,119 --> 01:22:19,997
So you got everything you wanted.
Happy?

954
01:22:20,199 --> 01:22:22,633
There's no money. I don't have a job.

955
01:22:22,839 --> 01:22:25,114
There's plenty of money now!

956
01:22:26,279 --> 01:22:29,351
See how great it worked out,
turning him in?

957
01:22:29,599 --> 01:22:31,794
I did it for you. For your own...

958
01:22:32,079 --> 01:22:35,435
You lie! You always lie.

959
01:22:37,039 --> 01:22:40,873
My father was a good man
and people liked him.

960
01:22:42,439 --> 01:22:44,828
Everyone liked him except you.

961
01:22:45,359 --> 01:22:47,748
You never liked me either.

962
01:22:48,079 --> 01:22:52,391
Then I find a grownup friend
of my own, and you know what?

963
01:22:53,199 --> 01:22:54,473
I loved him.

964
01:22:56,119 --> 01:23:00,158
You didn't just betray him;
you betrayed both of us.

965
01:23:10,479 --> 01:23:11,468
Bobby?

966
01:23:22,159 --> 01:23:23,990
Ted got it right.

967
01:23:24,199 --> 01:23:26,633
It isn 't all Atlantis.

968
01:23:28,199 --> 01:23:31,191
My mother got a job outside of Boston.

969
01:23:31,439 --> 01:23:34,795
And I was upset, of course,
but one thing...

970
01:23:34,999 --> 01:23:36,751
I wasn 't afraid.

971
01:23:37,159 --> 01:23:39,627
I had Ted to thank for that.

972
01:23:40,759 --> 01:23:43,751
Hey, get out of here.
This is my place now.

973
01:23:43,959 --> 01:23:46,314
You can't. This is everybody's park.

974
01:23:46,519 --> 01:23:48,111
Yes, I can.

975
01:23:51,279 --> 01:23:52,917
Little Bobby Garfield.

976
01:23:53,639 --> 01:23:56,597
Where's your fairy godfather
when you need him?

977
01:24:18,719 --> 01:24:21,153
That was for the Gerber Baby!

978
01:25:12,599 --> 01:25:14,396
Do you need any help?

979
01:25:14,639 --> 01:25:16,038
I'm fine.

980
01:25:35,959 --> 01:25:39,793
Do you think you could ever
see your way to forgiving me?

981
01:25:44,159 --> 01:25:46,468
I'm working on it, Mom.

982
01:26:15,239 --> 01:26:18,117
Carol, we're leaving now.

983
01:26:18,839 --> 01:26:20,238
Oh, no.

984
01:26:21,799 --> 01:26:24,438
Here. It's where I'll be
in Massachusetts.

985
01:26:24,679 --> 01:26:27,591
- Will you write to me?
- Of course.

986
01:26:27,799 --> 01:26:29,232
I'll write to you.

987
01:26:30,399 --> 01:26:32,708
I'll probably be homesick.

988
01:26:33,519 --> 01:26:35,669
I'll never forget you.

989
01:26:41,879 --> 01:26:44,393
Was it you who beat up Harry Doolin?

990
01:26:46,439 --> 01:26:47,588
Good.

991
01:26:48,639 --> 01:26:49,628
Good.

992
01:27:00,159 --> 01:27:02,275
- Carol, wait.
- I can't. Not now.

993
01:27:04,599 --> 01:27:07,238
- But l...
- I love you too, Bobby Garfield.

994
01:27:09,119 --> 01:27:11,269
But I have to go make the salad.

995
01:27:21,119 --> 01:27:23,872
9:35, 25 minutes before 1 0
on WKMD...

996
01:27:24,079 --> 01:27:27,310
...serving up the biggest hits
with the Platters.

997
01:27:35,439 --> 01:27:36,997
So, what are we gonna do?

998
01:27:37,199 --> 01:27:41,033
The best we can, Mom.
The best we can.

999
01:27:43,639 --> 01:27:46,028
Well, time and tide wait for no man.

1000
01:27:46,239 --> 01:27:49,151
Ben Jonson called time
"the old bald cheater. "

1001
01:27:49,359 --> 01:27:52,192
- Who was Ben Jonson?
- An English writer.

1002
01:27:52,399 --> 01:27:55,709
Foolish about money,
and given to flatulence.

1003
01:27:55,919 --> 01:27:57,591
Flatulence?

1004
01:27:59,119 --> 01:28:01,428
Bobby Garfield!

1005
01:28:30,519 --> 01:28:33,829
Hey!
I don't think you should be in there.

1006
01:28:34,159 --> 01:28:36,195
It's not safe.

1007
01:28:36,399 --> 01:28:39,152
I used to live here when I was a kid.

1008
01:28:43,199 --> 01:28:46,828
- Have you lived here long?
- Only my whole life.

1009
01:28:48,159 --> 01:28:50,992
Oh, wait a minute! Wait, wait, wait.

1010
01:28:54,479 --> 01:28:55,878
Was your mother...

1011
01:28:57,759 --> 01:28:59,750
...was she...?

1012
01:29:00,719 --> 01:29:03,756
Was she Carol, Carol Gerber?

1013
01:29:04,679 --> 01:29:08,957
- My mom's dead. She died years ago.
- I was sorry to hear that.

1014
01:29:12,039 --> 01:29:15,031
We never kept in touch
like we said we would.

1015
01:29:19,359 --> 01:29:21,589
My God.

1016
01:29:21,799 --> 01:29:24,267
You're the boy on the Ferris wheel?

1017
01:29:25,479 --> 01:29:30,792
- Mom told me about that.
- She promised she'd never tell anyone.

1018
01:29:32,079 --> 01:29:34,877
She said you were beautiful.

1019
01:29:38,279 --> 01:29:39,871
One of us was.

1020
01:30:13,719 --> 01:30:16,597
You can keep that, if you want.

1021
01:30:19,679 --> 01:30:20,953
I'm Bobby.

1022
01:30:22,799 --> 01:30:25,871
- Molly.
- Molly.

1023
01:30:31,439 --> 01:30:34,033
She had the heart of a lion.

1024
01:31:13,879 --> 01:31:17,269
I never heard from
Ted Brautigan again.

1025
01:31:17,479 --> 01:31:21,552
Not that I didn 't think of him.
I always have...

1026
01:31:21,759 --> 01:31:23,317
...and always will.

1027
01:31:25,159 --> 01:31:30,233
Because that summer was the last
of my childhood.

1028
01:31:31,119 --> 01:31:35,317
And though I never again saw
what people were thinking...

1029
01:31:35,519 --> 01:31:39,512
...there was an enduring gift
that he left me.

1030
01:31:40,519 --> 01:31:44,956
What Ted did was open my eyes...

1031
01:31:45,519 --> 01:31:47,749
...and let the future in.

1032
01:31:50,039 --> 01:31:52,678
I wouldn 't have missed a minute of it.

1033
01:31:53,999 --> 01:31:55,910
Not for all the world.

